"title": "5405: medicine",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5405",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The means that God has given for the cure of physical troubles. Medicine often symbolises the application of the gospel of God's grace in Jesus Christ for the healing of moral and spiritual ills.</p>\n<h2>Preventative medicine</h2>\n<h3>A cheerful disposition</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:22\">PRO 17:22</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Disinfection</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:41\">LEV 14:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:5\">LEV 15:5</a></p>\n<h3>Salt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:4\">EZK 16:4</a></p>\n<h3>Physical exercise</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:8\">1TI 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>Curative medicine</h2>\n<h3>Balm</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:8\">JER 51:8</a></strong> <em>An example of medicine used as a picture of the gospel. The nation had the cure for its ills in the mercy of God if only it would repent and turn to him.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:22\">JER 8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:11\">JER 46:11</a></p>\n<h3>Leaves</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:12\">EZK 47:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:2\">REV 22:2</a></p>\n<h3>Mud</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:6\">JHN 9:6</a> <em>The connection between the medium used and the cure is not always clear.  For example, the use of mud, spittle, oil and water appears sometimes to be more symbolic than practical.</em></p>\n<h3>Oil</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:13\">MRK 6:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:34\">LUK 10:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:14\">JAS 5:14</a></p>\n<h3>A poultice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:7\">2KI 20:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:21\">ISA 38:21</a></p>\n<h3>Spittle</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:33\">MRK 7:33</a></p>\n<h3>Water</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:5\">LEV 15:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:10\">2KI 5:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:7\">JHN 9:7</a></p>\n<h3>Wine</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:23\">1TI 5:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:34\">LUK 10:34</a></p>\n<h3>Eye salve</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:18\">REV 3:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Music</h3>\n<p>The music was intended to cure moods of depression in Saul's case, and extreme agitation in Elisha:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:23\">1SA 16:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:10\">1SA 18:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:14-2Kgs3:15\">2KI 3:14–3:15</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual surgery</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:27-Matt5:30\">MAT 5:27–5:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13\">ROM 8:13</a></p>\n<h2>Soothing medicine</h2>\n<h3>Myrrh</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:23\">MRK 15:23</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Oil</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:6\">ISA 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Wine</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:6\">PRO 31:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:48\">MAT 27:48</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:36\">LUK 23:36</a></p>\n<h2>Medicine cannot cure everything</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:27\">DEU 28:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:9\">JER 17:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:12-Jer30:13\">JER 30:12–30:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:11\">JER 46:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:25-Mark5:26\">MRK 5:25–5:26</a></p>\n<h2>Application of the gospel as medicine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:28\">MAT 11:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:31-Luke5:32\">LUK 5:31–5:32</a></p>\n<h2>Resurrection as the ultimate medicine for all ills</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:42-1Cor15:44\">1CO 15:42–15:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20-Phil3:21\">PHP 3:20–3:21</a></p>",
